This paper belongs to the field of computer security (cs.CR) as it focuses on studying the behavior of spammers and identifying social networks of spammers. Additionally, it involves data analysis and clustering techniques, which are commonly used in the subfield of computational social science (cs.SI). The paper also deals with large datasets and network analysis, which are relevant to the subfields of software engineering (cs.SD) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of data science (cs.DS).
